         <div xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191"><!-- p4l3-r4 -->
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Hd1e108">Rubrica 4</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De arrogantia: insolentia: iactantia et vanagloria</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>
      ¶ De arrogantia iactantia insolen
      <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>tia et vanagloria.  ¶ Rubrica. 4
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e121">
      
               <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>SAlomon in prouerbiis.
      <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>c. 16. <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e127">Abho
        <lb ed="#V" n="32" break="no"/>minatio domini est omnis arro
        <lb ed="#V" n="33" break="no"/>gans.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e135"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e137"> 24 c. Qui se iactat et dilatat
        <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>iurgia concitatur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e144"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e146"> Idem in ecclesiast. c. 7.
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>Melior est patiens arrogante. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e152">
               <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e156">¶ Aristotelis magnorum moralium: li. i. c. 52
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>Iactantior est plus eis que sunt sibi fingens
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>esse aut scire que non sciuit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e164">
               <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e168">¶ Oratius in poetria: Parturieut montes na
        <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>scetur ridiculus mus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e174">
               <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e178">¶ Tullius retho. artis vereris: lib. i. c. 12. Ex
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>arrogantia odium solet euenire: ex insolen
        <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>tia arrogantia. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e186">
               <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e190">¶ Quintillianus declamationum. 8 declam. <!--234.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>Insolentiam immeritam quoque potentiam car
        <lb ed="#V" n="46" break="no"/>pit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e202"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e204"> 17. et fi. declam. Pars voluptatis vi
        <lb ed="#V" n="47" break="no"/>detur esse iactatio. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e211">
               <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e215">¶ Seneca epistolarum ad lucillum: li. 12. et. e2
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>et fina. Diuitie insolentiam dant: nihil est
        <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>aliud insolentia quam spes false magnitudinis </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e223">
               <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e227">/ Idem de remedio fortuitorum. c. 21. et fi
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>na. Facilius reges animum nulla vanitate
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>rerum tumentium. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e235">
               <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e239">¶ Auctor scil de fortu. hone. vite. c. 2. Non
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>eris arrogans. Que nosti sine arrogantia po
        <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>stulanti imparties. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e247">
               <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e251">¶ Boetius in topicis. l. 3. Ex arrogantia fit
        <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>quisque odiosus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e257">
               <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e261">¶ Isydorus solliloquiorum: li. 2. c. 13 Ca
        <lb ed="#V" n="60" break="no"/>ue inanis glorie studium non te arroges: non
        <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>te iactes: non te insolenter extollas. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e269"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e271"> 28. c.
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>Magnus numquam videri studeas. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e278"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e280"> 44. c. Su
        <lb ed="#V" n="63" break="no"/>periori equalem te non exhibeas. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e286">
               <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e290">¶ Bernardus de improbatione vitiorum. c.
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>et. Uana superborum vacuat iactatio meniem. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e296">
               <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e300">¶ Gaufridus in poetria. c. 31. Cum fueris
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>maior aliis te finge minorem.
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>Et de te mentire tibi nec sic in abyssum.
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>Deitias alios vt te super ethera tollas
        <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>Uicat opus verbu: minuit iactantia famam </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e312">
               <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e316">/ Capitulo. 84
        <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>Utere consilio: led omnia noueris vnus
        <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>Maior in hc aliis: in verbis sis tantu vnus
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>Ex aliis: nec sis elati sed socialis
        <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>Eloquii: veterum clamat doctrina: loquaris
        <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>Ut plures: sapientias vt pauci. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e330">
               <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e334">¶ Iesus filius sirach: in ecclesiastco. 32. In
        <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>multis esto quasi inscius: et audi tacens si
        <lb ed="#V" n="79" break="no"/>mul et querens. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e342">
               <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e346">¶ Ouidius de tristibus: lih. i. e. i. Dum petit
        <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>infirmus nimium sublimia penis:
        <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>Icarus equoreas nomine fecit aquas. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e355">
               <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e359">¶ Seneca de ira: li. i. In ruinam prona sunt
        <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>que sine fundamentis creuere. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e365">
               <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e369">¶ Ualerius maximus: li. 4. t. de fiducia sua.
        <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>Laudata profecto siducia est que estima
        <lb ed="#V" n="87" break="no"/>tionem sui certo pondere examinat: tantum
        <lb ed="#V" n="88"/>sibi arrogans quantum a contemptum et inso
        <lb ed="#V" n="89" break="no"/>lentia distari satis est. <!--235.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="98-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
               </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e388">
               <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e392">¶ Marcialis cocus vel vndique suscepto. c. 2
        <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>Sepe ruis dumsepe petis nimis alta corona
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>Fac sit sufficiens vna ruina tibi. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e400"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e402"> Capistolo. 3
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>Altior assensus grauior plerumque ruina est.
        <lb ed="#V" n="5"/>Sollicitudo grauis est preparatus honor
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>Cum nimis alta petis citus incautusque ruina
        <lb ed="#V" n="7"/>Et grauis et subita est secte timenda tibi. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e414">
               <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e418">¶ Uegetius de re militari: li. 3. t. 6. Interdum
        <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>imperita rusticitas. plura promittit: et credit
        <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>se scire que nescit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e426">
               <lb ed="#V" n="11"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e430">¶ Aucto vel de for. hone. vite. c. 2. Non altio
        <lb ed="#V" n="12" break="no"/>ri rei te imponas in qua statim tibi ascendem
        <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>ti tremendum: descendenti cadendum sit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e439">
               <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e443">¶ Cassiodorus epistolarum: li. 5. e. 13. Igno
        <lb ed="#V" n="15"/>rat modum seruare presumptio nec potest
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>sub modo redigi cum licentia suerit visa concedi. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e451">
               <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e455">¶ Uersificator fabularum esopi. 36 f. Qui
        <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>plus posse putat sua quam natura ministrat
        <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>Posse suum superans se minus ipse potest. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e463">
               <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e467">¶ Baldo. 29 fabula: Non vltra vires di
        <lb ed="#V" n="21" break="no"/>scant presumere viles. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e473">
               <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e477">¶ Mattheus vindoc. in poetria ptur. i. c. 6.
        <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>Inconsulta nocet presumptio fallitur errat:
        <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>Naturale putans dilapidare bonum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e485">
               <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e489">¶ Gaufridus in potria. c. 31. Et vires metie
        <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>re tuas: si fortis es aude
        <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>Grandia: si fragilis: humeris in pone minori
        <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>Si mediocris: ama mediocria: sumere noli
        <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>Que quando sumis presumas </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-d1e501">
               <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d78191-Qd1e505">¶ Prouerb. vulg Chi piu montache non de
        <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>pium tosto cade che non cre. </quote>
            </p>
         </div>
